rComments: Cassandra is a great professor. Her lectures were very insightful and I was thoroughly engaged every time. She takes the extra time to answer questions and really does care about her students. The weekly quizzes were very fair and we were given a choice between the final paper or exam. It was a great experience and I learned a lot!

She is a pretty fair Prof who is more than willing to take feedback from her student in regards to the course material and grading scheme. In fact she even changed how she graded her quizzes as well as how much time we were given to complete them because of feedback from the class a few weeks into the course. She really wants students to succeed.

Cassandra is a fantastic prof! She really cares about her students and does everything in power to ensure they are successful. Even with 9 am online lectures, she does her very best to be interesting and keep everyone engaged! We had weekly quizzes for assessment (very fair), discussions, and a choice between the final paper or exam. Great class!

Cassandra is one of the best profs I ever had. This class was the one I was least excited for and ended up being my favourite. She is caring and funny and the lectures are so interesting. She does Kahoots and you will get participation marks. Also during Covid-19 situation, was one of few profs to continue making us top quality online lectures.
Cassandra is great, she is clear about her expectations in the course and she is engaging as a prof. Very fair when it comes to marking, all you have to do is study the material and UNDERSTAND it.
Cassandra is very understanding and is clear about her expectations for this class. The content is interesting and Cassandra has a lot of interesting stories to back up what you learn.

Class has 2 midterms with choice of an assignment, as well as 1 final. Kahoot questions to complete each class for easy participation marks. No textbook for her class. Great prof with realistic expectations and interesting lectures. PhD student that remembers what its like being a student and cares about our success in her course. 100% recommend.
